# Phosphor Icon Naming

Imports from `phosphor-svelte` must use a local name ending in **`Icon`**. The import path stays the Phosphor export name (no `Icon` in the path unless Phosphor provides it).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
import Bell from 'phosphor-svelte/lib/Bell';
import X from 'phosphor-svelte/lib/X';
import TextUnderline from 'phosphor-svelte/lib/TextUnderline';

// ✅ GOOD
import BellIcon from 'phosphor-svelte/lib/Bell';
import XIcon from 'phosphor-svelte/lib/X';
import TextUnderlineIcon from 'phosphor-svelte/lib/TextUnderline';
```

Use the same `Icon` suffix in markup:

```svelte
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<Bell size={20} />

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<BellIcon size={20} />
```

When adding or editing icon imports in `packages/app`, rename the binding to `{Name}Icon` and update all usages in that file.
